
"RPC" stands for remote procedural call. In this experiment, it allows one linux machine to use another linux machine as compute participant. 
It will help establish a baseline for future distributed compute experiments. It is commonly used as a tool for distributing inference.

## Test Setup

The RPC setup used two Linux machines connected over Ethernet.
- Node count: 2 Linux machines
- Connection: Ethernet
- Framework: Llama.cpp with RPC support
- Model: Llama 3B Q4_K_M
- Benchmark tool: `llama-bench`

For edge-AI systems, it may be useful to distribute inference workloads across multiple Linux-based nodes. However, distributed execution introduces overhead.


This experiment was designed to observe whether RPC meaningfully changed inference throughput and real-time execution behavior.

